Voice-Activated Assistant

Welcome to the Voice-Activated Assistant repository! This project demonstrates a voice-controlled assistant implemented in Python, capable of performing various tasks based on voice commands.

Features

- Speech Recognition: Uses the SpeechRecognition library to convert speech to text.
- Text-to-Speech: Employs Pyttsx3 to provide spoken responses.
- Wikipedia Integration: Retrieves information from Wikipedia based on user queries.
- WolframAlpha Integration: Computes answers to factual queries using the WolframAlpha API.
- Web Browsing: Enables seamless web browsing via Chrome.
- Note-Taking: Allows users to record notes, timestamped and stored as text files.

