Check out the video demonstration of the Voice-Activated Assistant in action: [Insert Video Link Here]

Getting Started

To run the assistant locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/voice-activated-assistant.git
   cd voice-activated-assistant
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

3. Set up APIs:
   - Obtain API keys for WolframAlpha and ensure access to Wikipedia.

4. Run the application:
   ```bash
   python voice_assistant.py
   ```
